on of the AF/O order is evidence that the phases are competing. At\nhigher doping, superconductivity has a maximum Tc of 38 K at x = 0.4 falling to\n3 K at x = 1.0. We discuss reasons for the suppression of the spin-density-wave\norder and the electron-hole asymmetry in the phase diagram.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 May 2012 16:56:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-05-08"}
